Expense Ratio (Net)
Net Expense Ratio is the total annual operating expense from the fund's most recent prospectus after any fee waiver and/or expense reimbursements that will reduce any fund operating expenses for no less than one year from the effective date of the fund's registration statement. This number does not include any fee waiver arrangement or expense reimbursement that may be terminated without agreement of the fund's board of trustees during the one-year period.

Expense Ratio (Gross)
For a mutual fund, the expense ratio is the total annual fund or class operating expenses (before waivers or reimbursements) paid by the fund and stated as a percent of the fund's total net assets. Mutual fund data has been drawn from the most recent prospectus.

1, 3, 5, and 10Yr performance numbers quoted are average annual total returns. These figures do not include the effect of sales charges, if any. Should a fund charge a sales load, standard quarter- end and other load-adjust performance is available by clicking on the fund name.
